<GV>
TREASURY DEPARTMENT (TRE)
</GV>
<LP>
   WASHINGTON -- The Treasury plans to pay down about $4.95
billion on the federal debt with the sale Monday of about
$17.2 billion in short-term bills. Maturing bills
outstanding, including 20-day cash management bills, total
$22.14 billion.
   The offering will be divided evenly between 13-week and
26-week bills, which will be dated June 21 and will mature
Sept. 20 and Dec. 20, 1990, respectively.
</LP>
